---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="About"
  description="Why Paintings Explained exists — making the hidden details in great art visible to everyone."
>
  <section class="section container about">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>Great paintings are full of secrets. We point them out.</h1>
    <p>
      People stand in front of certain paintings for hours. Not because of the
      brushwork alone, but because the longer you look, the more you find — a
      hidden skull, a self-portrait tucked into a crowd, a coded message in a
      mirror, a gesture that changes the whole story.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Paintings Explained</strong> collects those masterpieces and shows
      you exactly what to look for. Zoom into ultra–high-resolution images, tap
      the markers to reveal hidden details, and read short, plain-language
      explanations of why each painting rewards a slow, careful look.
    </p>
    <p>
      Every image here is in the public domain (CC0), drawn from the open-access
      collections of <a href="https://www.metmuseum.org/about-the-met/policies-and-documents/open-access" rel="noopener">The Metropolitan Museum of Art</a>
      and the <a href="https://www.artic.edu/open-access/open-access-images" rel="noopener">Art Institute of Chicago</a> —
      so you're free to look as closely as you like.
    </p>
    <p><a class="btn btn--primary" href="/paintings">Start exploring</a></p>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .about { max-width: 760px; display: grid; gap: var(--space-4); }
  .about h1 { margin-block: var(--space-2) var(--space-4); }
  .about p { font-size: var(--fs-500); }
  .about .btn { margin-top: var(--space-4); }
</style>
